{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": 1,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Now these were the sons of David, which were born unto him in Hebron;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "the firstborn Amnon, of Ahinoam the Jezreelitess; the second Daniel, of Abigail the Carmelitess:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Daniel: or, Chileab"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 2,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The third, Absalom the son of Maachah the daughter of Talmai king of Geshur: the fourth, Adonijah the son of Haggith:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 3,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The fifth, Shephatiah of Abital: the sixth, Ithream by Eglah his wife."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 4,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "These six were born unto him in Hebron; and there he reigned seven years and six months: and in Jerusalem he reigned thirty and three years."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 5,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And these were born unto him in Jerusalem; Shimea, and Shobab, and Nathan, and Solomon, four, of Bath-shua the daughter of Ammiel:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Shimea: or, Shammua",
        "Bath-shua: or, Bath-sheba",
        "Ammiel: or, Eliam"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 6,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Ibhar also, and Elishama, and Eliphelet,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Elishama: also called, Elishua"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 7,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Nogah, and Nepheg, and Japhia,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 8,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Elishama, and Eliada, and Eliphelet, nine."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Eliada: or, Beeliada"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 9,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "These were all the sons of David, beside the sons of the concubines, and Tamar their sister."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 10,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Solomon's son was Rehoboam, Abia his son, Asa his son, Jehoshaphat his son,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Abia: or, Abijam"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Solomon's Descendants"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 11,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Joram his son, Ahaziah his son, Joash his son,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Ahaziah: or, Azariah"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 12,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Amaziah his son, Azariah his son, Jotham his son,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Azariah: or, Uzziah"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 13,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Ahaz his son, Hezekiah his son, Manasseh his son,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 14,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Amon his son, Josiah his son."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 15,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the sons of Josiah were, the firstborn Johanan, the second Jehoiakim, the third Zedekiah, the fourth Shallum."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Johanan: or, Jehoahaz",
        "Jehoiakim: or, Eliakim",
        "Zedekiah: or, Mattaniah"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 16,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the sons of Jehoiakim: Jeconiah his son, Zedekiah his son."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Jeconiah: also called, Jehoiachin or Coniah"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 17,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the sons of Jeconiah; Assir, Salathiel his son,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Salathiel: Heb. Shealtiel"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Descendants of Jeconiah"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 18,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Malchiram also, and Pedaiah, and Shenazar, Jecamiah, Hoshama, and Nedabiah."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 19,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the sons of Pedaiah were, Zerubbabel, and Shimei: and the sons of Zerubbabel; Meshullam, and Hananiah, and Shelomith their sister:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 20,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Hashubah, and Ohel, and Berechiah, and Hasadiah, Jushab-hesed, five."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 21,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the sons of Hananiah; Pelatiah, and Jesaiah: the sons of Rephaiah, the sons of Arnan, the sons of Obadiah, the sons of Shechaniah."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 22,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the sons of Shechaniah; Shemaiah: and the sons of Shemaiah; Hattush, and Igeal, and Bariah, and Neariah, and Shaphat, six."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 23,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the sons of Neariah; Elioenai, and Hezekiah, and Azrikam, three."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "Hezekiah: Heb. Hiskijah"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 24,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the sons of Elioenai were, Hodaiah, and Eliashib, and Pelaiah, and Akkub, and Johanan, and Dalaiah, and Anani, seven."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    }
  ]
}